msgstr ""
"If you want to exchange data between two OBP60 devices via Wi-Fi, both "
"devices must be on the same wireless network and have different system "
"names. Your access points must be in the same IP address range but have "
"different device addresses. One device must be configured as a TCP server "
"and the other as a TCP client. These settings are configured under "
":ref:`Config - System`. Failure to follow these instructions may result in "
"Wi-Fi data traffic disruptions and you may lose access to the devices' web "
"configuration interfaces."

